{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionPredicting molecular properties is central to applications such as drug discovery or material design.",
    "Without accurate prediction of properties such as toxicity, a promising drug candidate is likely to fail clinical trials.",
    "Many molecular properties cannot be feasibly computed (simulated) from first principles as their complexity scales with at least the 4th power of the number of atoms.",
    "It makes computation infeasible for even moderately large systems.",
    "Moreover, complex molecular properties, such as predicting the yield of chemical reactions, are still beyond the reach of what is typically referred to as computational chemistry methods [1]."
  ]
}